Instagram Beauty Influencer Engagement Analysis

1. My Contribution
   Designed and implemented caption feature engineering pipeline from raw text data
   
   Performed multimodal regression analysis (text + image features)
   
   Conducted data visualization and exploratory analysis
   
   Built presentation slides and contributed to final group presentation
   
   Translated statistical results into business-oriented insights for non-technical stakeholders

2. Tools & Methods
Python | R | Excel | VADER Sentiment Analysis | OLS Regression | Data Visualization | Feature Engineering

3. Overview
This project analyses 9,737 Instagram beauty influencer posts using a multimodal dataset combining caption text and image features. The objective is to understand how different content characteristics influence post-level engagement (likes + comments/followers).

The study applies multiple OLS regression models to compare explanatory power across text, image, and combined feature sets, as well as across influencer tiers (micro, mid, macro).

4. Research Objective
To examine how caption and image features jointly explain variations in engagement rate across different influencer tiers in Instagram beauty content.

5. Dataset
   9,737 Instagram beauty influencer posts
   Source: Kim et al. (WSDM 2021)
   Variables include caption text, image attributes, and engagement metrics
   Influencers grouped into micro, mid, and macro tiers

6. Feature Engineering
Caption Features (Text Analysis)
Extracted from raw Instagram captions:
   Sentiment score (VADER)
   Caption length (character count)
   Hashtag count
   Emoji count
   Call-to-action (CTA) indicator
Output dataset: beauty_posts_caption.csv

7. Image Features (Visual Analysis)
   Brightness
   Colorfulness
   Face presence
   Edge density

8. Methodology
   Regression Models (OLS)
   Caption-only model
   Image-only model
   Combined multimodal model
Tier-stratified models (micro/mid/macro influencers)
OLS regression was selected for the interpretability of feature effects across different content modalities.

9. Key Findings
   Content features explain a limited proportion of engagement variance (R² ≈ 0.02–0.03)
   Image and caption features contribute differently depending on influencer tier
   Face presence and sentiment show weak but consistent associations with engagement
   Macro influencer models exhibit lower stability due to smaller sample size

10. Limitations
   Cross-sectional dataset (no time-series dynamics)
   Platform-specific bias (Instagram only)
   Low explanatory power, indicating strong influence of external factors (e.g. algorithm, timing)
   Correlation does not imply causation


